column1: 717616822,GSoC 2021 - Final Submission Pull Request,"# Google Summer of Code - 2021 with ODK-X
- **Organisation** - Digital Impact Alliance (DIAL) at UN Foundation

- **Mentors** - Waylon Brunette ([@wbrunette](https://github.com/wbrunette)), Lakshya Gupta ([@lakshyagupta21](https://github.com/lakshyagupta21)),  Jeff Beorse ([@jbeorse](https://github.com/jbeorse)) and Li Lin ([@linl33](https://github.com/linl33))

This summer, I was fortunate to become a part of the Google Summer of Code, where I worked as a student to improve the User-Interface and the Authentication Workflow of the Services Application and upgrade the existing Java Technology.

Earlier, the ODK-X Toolsuite Android Applications users had to perform several steps to authenticate and log out the Services Application. The User-Interface and the User-Experience were also not up to the mark and required significant improvements to match the current UI/UX Standards.

column2: - Added the Different Properties required during the Authentication Workflow.
- Updated the Default Values of the Properties.
- The Main Repository where features were implemented.
- **Pull Requests** - This Pull Request itself contains all the work done from the starting of the Coding Period.

- Designed the new User-Interface for the following Screens in all the User States -  ***Main Screen***, ***Sync Screen***, ***Login Screen***, ***Verify Screen*** and ***Update Server Settings Screen***.
- Links to the Documents and Tools Used -
- Divided the existing Authentication Workflow into 2 parts - ***Server Authentication/Verification*** and ***User Authentication/Verification***.

column3: - Verifying if Server supports Anonymous Users or not
- Implemented the **[JetPack Lifecycle Listeners](https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/architecture/lifecycle)** in all the Activities and Fragments of the Application.

- Added **[ViewModels](https://developer.android.com/topic/libraries/architecture/viewmodel)** for consistent Data Management in the Sync Processes and for allowing the automatic update of User-Interface in all the activities and fragments.

- Replaced the existing **Fragment Transaction** method with **[Navigation Component](https://developer.android.com/guide/navigation/navigation-getting-started)** to navigate between different Fragment Destinations.

column2: - Added Test Cases for verifying the Properties on the Startup.

- Added Automated UI Tests using [Espresso](https://developer.android.com/training/testing/ui-testing/espresso-testing) for all the 4 Activities in all the User States - ***MainActivity***, ***LoginActivity***, ***SyncActivity*** and ***VerifyServerSettingsActivity***.

column1: The major challenge I faced during the Coding Period was that few of the features took more than the expected time in their implementation. And due to this, I had to miss a few minor features implementation such as Upgrading the Notification Status and few Test Cases.

I got to learn a lot during my 2 months of GSoC. I gained a lot of Technical Knowledge in Android and Java which helped me to be updated with the Latest Technology in use and improved my skills as an Android Developer. I also got to learn a lot about how the people in the Industry Work and thus helped me to gain some Industry Experience.

I would continue to contribute to ODK-X. Currently, my target would be to completely implement the Final Product before it could be merged with the Master Branch. I would also work on extending the new User-Interface to other parts of the Services Application and other Toolsuite Applications. I would also be upgrading the ODK-X Docs after the final product is implemented.

The past 2 months were one of my greatest periods of learning. I gained a lot of Technical Knowledge and also got to work on Industry-Based Products. I would like to once again thank my mentors - [Waylon Brunette](https://github.com/wbrunette) and [Lakshya Gupta](https://github.com/lakshyagupta21) for constantly guiding me and supporting me during the Coding Period.
I would love to contribute more to ODK-X in the future.
